 Mapping is a data structure used to store data in key-value pairs. Each key is linked to one value.

Key → simple type (like address, uint).

Value → can be any type (number, bool, struct).

If a key is not set, it returns the default value.

You cannot loop through all keys, only access by key.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Common uses:

Storing user balances in tokens.

Checking if someone has voted or not.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

example ---:      //SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

contract demo {
    mapping(uint=>string) public roll_no;

function setter (uint keys , string  memory value) public
    {
                                   
     roll_no[keys]=value;
    }
}
  
